Package source.camp

Class Camp

java.lang.Object
source.camp.Camp
public class Camp extends Object
Represents a camp. A camp has students (association), enquries and suggestions (composition).
Since:
2023-11-10

    • getEnquiries

      public ArrayList<Enquiry> getEnquiries(boolean active, boolean notReplied)
      get a arrayList of filtered enquiries regarding this camp.
      Parameters:
      active - True for only active enquiries, false for both active and deleted enquiries.
      notReplied - True for only not replied enquiries, false for both replied and not replied enquiries.
      Returns:
      ArrayList of filtered enquiries.

    • addParticipant

      public void addParticipant(Student student, boolean committeeRole)
      Add a participant to the camp. This will increment the corresponding counter.
      Parameters:
      student - The student to be added into the camp.
      committeeRole - True for camp committee, false for camp attendee.

    • addWithdrawnParticipant

      public void addWithdrawnParticipant(Student student)
      Add a participant to the withdrawn list of the camp.

      Unlike withdrawParticipant(), this method neither remove the student from the participant list nor decrement the numAttendees counter.

      Parameters:
      student - The attendee to be added into the withdrawn list.

    • withdrawParticipant

      public void withdrawParticipant(Student student)
      Withdraw an participant from the camp.

      Unlike addWithdrawnParticipant(), this method remove the student from the participant list and decrement the numAttendees counter. //* @param attendee The attendee to withdraw.

    • viewDetailedCampInfo

      public void viewDetailedCampInfo(User user)
      Print out the detailed information of this camp, which includes the current committee members and attendees.

      This can only be done by the commmittee of this camp or any staff.

      Parameters:
      user - The user who attempts to view.
      Throws:
      NoAccessException - If user does not have access to the information.

    • deleteCamp

      public void deleteCamp(Staff staffInCharge)
      Delete this camp by setting active as false. Inactive camp will not be written back to csv.
      Parameters:
      staffInCharge - The staff who attempts to delete.
      Throws:
      NoAccessException - If staff is not the owner of this camp //* @throws CampNotFoundExceptions If this camp has already been deleted.

    • toggleVisibility

      public boolean toggleVisibility(Staff staffInCharge)
      Toggle the visibility of this camp (Not visible <-> Visible). Visibility can be toggled iff no students have signed up for this camp yet.
      Parameters:
      staffInCharge - The staff who attempts to toggle.
      Returns:
      The new visibility of this camp.
      Throws:
      NoAccessException - If staff is not the owner of this camp, or if students have already signed up for this camp.
